WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:12.345 --> 00:00:13.972 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU gasps]

00:00:14.055 --> 00:00:16.391 position:50% align:center
This bamboo forest
is so amazing!

00:00:16.474 --> 00:00:18.560 position:50% align:center
The autumn leaves are beautiful.

00:00:18.643 --> 00:00:21.438 position:50% align:center
Yes, they are.

00:00:21.521 --> 00:00:24.399 position:50% align:center
In fact, they've inspired
me to write a haiku.

00:00:24.482 --> 00:00:27.652 position:50% align:center
Heh. How does it go?
You have to let us hear.

00:00:27.736 --> 00:00:29.654 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:00:29.738 --> 00:00:32.574 position:50% align:center
My very educated mother
just served us noodles.

00:00:32.657 --> 00:00:34.743 position:50% align:center
--Not a haiku.
--All you think about is food.

00:00:34.826 --> 00:00:37.078 position:50% align:center
Oh. Let me try one!

00:00:37.162 --> 00:00:39.456 position:50% align:center
Please excuse my
dear aunt Sally.

00:00:39.539 --> 00:00:42.792 position:50% align:center
Oh, good one.
Far superior to mine.

00:00:42.876 --> 00:00:45.337 position:50% align:center
I graciously concede
this round to you.

00:00:45.420 --> 00:00:46.838 position:50% align:center
[HANAJIMA chuckles]

00:00:46.921 --> 00:00:49.466 position:50% align:center
[KYO, UOTANI] Neither of those
were even close to haikus!

00:00:49.549 --> 00:00:51.176 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU]
This is Kyoto.

00:00:51.259 --> 00:00:56.473 position:50% align:center
We're here to learn and
explore all it has to offer.

00:00:56.556 --> 00:01:01.269 position:50% align:center
Yes, our school trip
has finally begun!

00:02:33.445 --> 00:02:35.113 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
I dunno about this.

00:02:35.196 --> 00:02:37.073 position:50% align:center
Doesn't seem like the kinda
place you wanna visit

00:02:37.157 --> 00:02:39.659 position:50% align:center
with a whole big group
of people, if you ask me.

00:02:39.743 --> 00:02:41.619 position:50% align:center
Sorta ruins the
atmosphere, ya know?

00:02:41.703 --> 00:02:44.330 position:50% align:center
You realize it wouldn't
be much of a class trip

00:02:44.414 --> 00:02:46.124 position:50% align:center
without the class here for it.

00:02:46.207 --> 00:02:49.210 position:50% align:center
It's torture not being allowed
to eat whatever I wish.

00:02:49.294 --> 00:02:50.545 position:50% align:center
I want some herring soba.

00:02:50.628 --> 00:02:51.963 position:50% align:center
You love your food.

00:02:52.047 --> 00:02:55.175 position:50% align:center
Tell ya what, ladies,
we'll plan another trip here.

00:02:55.258 --> 00:02:56.801 position:50% align:center
Just for us girls, though.

00:02:56.885 --> 00:02:58.053 position:50% align:center
Sounds wonderful.

00:02:58.136 --> 00:02:59.512 position:50% align:center
That would be fun.

00:02:59.596 --> 00:03:02.515 position:50% align:center
Can we spend longer checking
out the temples next time?

00:03:02.599 --> 00:03:04.351 position:50% align:center
We'll do whatever we want.

00:03:04.434 --> 00:03:06.728 position:50% align:center
Take a relaxing stroll
around the gardens.

00:03:06.811 --> 00:03:09.606 position:50% align:center
Eat delicious food
from every restaurant.

00:03:09.689 --> 00:03:11.524 position:50% align:center
[HANAJIMA, UOTANI]
And maybe witness a murder.

00:03:11.608 --> 00:03:12.567 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU yelps]

00:03:12.650 --> 00:03:15.570 position:50% align:center
They watch too much TV.

00:03:15.653 --> 00:03:18.031 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU] I'm enjoying the trip
a lot now that we're here,

00:03:18.114 --> 00:03:20.992 position:50% align:center
but honestly, everything
that's happened lately

00:03:21.076 --> 00:03:22.827 position:50% align:center
had me so distracted

00:03:22.911 --> 00:03:25.580 position:50% align:center
that I completely forgot
it was coming up.

00:03:26.873 --> 00:03:28.124 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE]
What's this?

00:03:28.208 --> 00:03:30.210 position:50% align:center
Retiring to your room
for the night already?

00:03:30.293 --> 00:03:32.128 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah.

00:03:32.212 --> 00:03:34.089 position:50% align:center
There's some research
I want to do,

00:03:34.172 --> 00:03:36.299 position:50% align:center
and I should start getting
ready for the trip.

00:03:36.383 --> 00:03:40.220 position:50% align:center
Wait. What was that?
You're going on a trip, Yuki?

00:03:40.303 --> 00:03:44.140 position:50% align:center
Miss Honda, did you forget
about our class trip?

00:03:44.224 --> 00:03:44.974 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:03:45.058 --> 00:03:46.267 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
You, too, Cat?

00:03:46.351 --> 00:03:48.395 position:50% align:center
I didn't even wanna go
on it in the first place.

00:03:48.478 --> 00:03:49.437 position:50% align:center
It sounds boring.

00:03:49.521 --> 00:03:50.897 position:50% align:center
Oh, no! This is terrible!

00:03:50.980 --> 00:03:53.400 position:50% align:center
I haven't done anything
to get ready yet!

00:03:53.483 --> 00:03:54.943 position:50% align:center
Shigure, quick!

00:03:55.026 --> 00:03:57.612 position:50% align:center
I need some ideas of what to
bring you back as a souvenir.

00:03:57.696 --> 00:03:59.072 position:50% align:center
Forget about me.

00:03:59.155 --> 00:04:01.825 position:50% align:center
I'd much rather you focus
on having a good time, 'kay?

00:04:01.908 --> 00:04:03.743 position:50% align:center
School trips are
important milestones

00:04:03.827 --> 00:04:05.704 position:50% align:center
in a student's life, right?

00:04:05.787 --> 00:04:07.831 position:50% align:center
Well... yeah.

00:04:07.914 --> 00:04:10.250 position:50% align:center
You must get a souvenir
for yourself, though.

00:04:10.333 --> 00:04:11.334 position:50% align:center
Pick something yet?

00:04:11.418 --> 00:04:13.795 position:50% align:center
Oh, yes. Some figurines.

00:04:13.878 --> 00:04:16.131 position:50% align:center
What's the big deal
about some dumb trip?

00:04:16.214 --> 00:04:18.717 position:50% align:center
Sounds like more trouble
than it's worth to me.

00:04:18.800 --> 00:04:19.968 position:50% align:center
Maybe I'll just ditch.

00:04:20.051 --> 00:04:20.885 position:50% align:center
You idiot!

00:04:20.969 --> 00:04:22.387 position:50% align:center
Ow!

00:04:22.470 --> 00:04:24.514 position:50% align:center
Class trips are essential!
They're the essence of romance!

00:04:24.597 --> 00:04:26.433 position:50% align:center
The highlight of
one's school career!

00:04:26.516 --> 00:04:28.435 position:50% align:center
Young people lose
their inhibitions,

00:04:28.518 --> 00:04:30.145 position:50% align:center
feel free to confess their love,

00:04:30.228 --> 00:04:32.439 position:50% align:center
and who knows where
that might lead?

00:04:32.522 --> 00:04:35.025 position:50% align:center
Hey, don't you walk
away from me!

00:04:36.276 --> 00:04:38.611 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU]
It worked out in the end.

00:04:38.695 --> 00:04:40.864 position:50% align:center
I rushed frantically
to prepare for the trip

00:04:40.947 --> 00:04:44.200 position:50% align:center
and arrived in Kyoto
without a problem.

00:04:44.284 --> 00:04:45.660 position:50% align:center
Look at this place.

00:04:45.744 --> 00:04:48.329 position:50% align:center
I wish I could show Mom.
She'd love it here.

00:04:48.413 --> 00:04:50.331 position:50% align:center
[HIROSHI]
Psst. Hey, man, check it out.

00:04:50.415 --> 00:04:52.500 position:50% align:center
The first new couple
of the class trip!

00:04:52.584 --> 00:04:54.753 position:50% align:center
[YUSUKE]
Ooh! Look at 'em go!

00:04:54.836 --> 00:04:56.463 position:50% align:center
Why do so many
people get together

00:04:56.546 --> 00:04:58.131 position:50% align:center
during these things d'you think?

00:04:58.214 --> 00:04:58.965 position:50% align:center
It's the mood.

00:04:59.049 --> 00:04:59.674 position:50% align:center
[YUSUKE, HIROSHI grunt]

00:04:59.758 --> 00:05:00.967 position:50% align:center
I want in on that.

00:05:01.051 --> 00:05:02.260 position:50% align:center
Someone confess to me!

00:05:02.344 --> 00:05:03.595 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU chuckles]

00:05:03.678 --> 00:05:05.263 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU] I wonder if that's
what Shigure was like

00:05:05.347 --> 00:05:06.556 position:50% align:center
when he was younger.

00:05:06.639 --> 00:05:10.226 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
Confessions of love. Right.

00:05:11.394 --> 00:05:14.356 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU]
Uo- <i>chan</i> still doesn't know.

00:05:14.439 --> 00:05:18.818 position:50% align:center
I haven't told her that her
Kureno is Kureno Soma.

00:05:18.902 --> 00:05:21.654 position:50% align:center
I can't. Not yet.

00:05:21.738 --> 00:05:24.574 position:50% align:center
[KURENO] I don't plan
to see her again. Ever.

00:05:25.617 --> 00:05:29.954 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU] I will, but...
I haven't found the right time.

00:05:30.038 --> 00:05:30.622 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
Tohru.

00:05:30.705 --> 00:05:32.457 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Uh, yes?

00:05:32.540 --> 00:05:34.834 position:50% align:center
Don'tcha think it's kinda weird?

00:05:34.918 --> 00:05:37.170 position:50% align:center
If tons've people are
professing their love,

00:05:37.253 --> 00:05:39.923 position:50% align:center
shouldn't our prince here
be surrounded by girls?

00:05:40.006 --> 00:05:42.842 position:50% align:center
Where're his adoring fans?

00:05:42.926 --> 00:05:45.762 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU]
Huh. Now that you mention it...

00:05:45.845 --> 00:05:49.974 position:50% align:center
I'm just not as popular as you
think I am, Uotani. Sorry.

00:05:50.058 --> 00:05:52.185 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
Yeah, we'll see about that.

00:05:52.268 --> 00:05:53.603 position:50% align:center
[KINOSHITA]
Fear not.

00:05:53.687 --> 00:05:57.482 position:50% align:center
In the shadows and in
the light, we're here.

00:05:57.565 --> 00:06:00.235 position:50% align:center
The Prince Yuki Fan Club
will protect you!

00:06:00.318 --> 00:06:02.570 position:50% align:center
[IWATA] We must put the greater
good ahead of our desire

00:06:02.654 --> 00:06:03.780 position:50% align:center
to get closer to you.

00:06:03.863 --> 00:06:05.281 position:50% align:center
[CHIE sighs]

00:06:05.365 --> 00:06:08.034 position:50% align:center
[CHIE] Though I am secretly
plotting my own confession.

00:06:08.118 --> 00:06:10.078 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] Seriously, Kyo's
the one popular one.

00:06:10.161 --> 00:06:11.287 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:06:11.371 --> 00:06:13.415 position:50% align:center
A girl actually pulled
him aside just now.

00:06:13.498 --> 00:06:16.584 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI] Huh? Hey,
you're right. He's gone.

00:06:16.668 --> 00:06:18.169 position:50% align:center
Let's go! I gotta see this.

00:06:18.253 --> 00:06:20.046 position:50% align:center
[HIROSHI] Wait, you mean
we're gonna spy on him?

00:06:20.130 --> 00:06:21.089 position:50% align:center
[YUSUKE]
Count me in!

00:06:21.172 --> 00:06:22.132 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU gasps]

00:06:22.215 --> 00:06:23.967 position:50% align:center
Um. You, too, Hana- <i>chan</i> ?

00:06:24.050 --> 00:06:27.303 position:50% align:center
Miss Honda, why don't we
go on ahead without them?

00:06:27.387 --> 00:06:29.389 position:50% align:center
Uh. But I--

00:06:29.472 --> 00:06:33.727 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] Don't worry.
He'll say no. I'm sure of it.

00:06:37.897 --> 00:06:39.232 position:50% align:center
[KYO]
Will you listen?

00:06:39.315 --> 00:06:41.985 position:50% align:center
However you might feel about
me, I'm not interested.

00:06:42.068 --> 00:06:43.778 position:50% align:center
I don't even know your name.

00:06:43.862 --> 00:06:45.864 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT A] I can tell you
my name easily enough.

00:06:45.947 --> 00:06:46.573 position:50% align:center
And who knows...?

00:06:46.656 --> 00:06:47.699 position:50% align:center
They're mid-confession!

00:06:47.782 --> 00:06:49.034 position:50% align:center
It's a hot mess.

00:06:49.117 --> 00:06:50.869 position:50% align:center
Oh, man. From the sound of it,

00:06:50.952 --> 00:06:53.329 position:50% align:center
Kyon's pretty pissed
about the situation.

00:06:53.413 --> 00:06:55.290 position:50% align:center
I figured he'd just
be embarrassed.

00:06:55.373 --> 00:06:56.833 position:50% align:center
I'm bearing my heart
and soul to you

00:06:56.916 --> 00:06:58.376 position:50% align:center
and that's all you have to say?

00:06:58.460 --> 00:06:59.627 position:50% align:center
Hey!

00:07:01.254 --> 00:07:05.342 position:50% align:center
Don't touch me.
You're so damn annoying.

00:07:05.425 --> 00:07:08.636 position:50% align:center
Why the hell would you be
interested in someone like me?

00:07:08.720 --> 00:07:09.929 position:50% align:center
Are you stupid?

00:07:10.013 --> 00:07:11.890 position:50% align:center
You moron!

00:07:11.973 --> 00:07:13.933 position:50% align:center
Hold on, what are you
guys doing here?

00:07:14.017 --> 00:07:16.978 position:50% align:center
You can't go around treating
girls like that, you big brute!

00:07:17.062 --> 00:07:18.313 position:50% align:center
Yeah, handle with care!

00:07:18.396 --> 00:07:20.857 position:50% align:center
A real man is always
gentle with the ladies.

00:07:20.940 --> 00:07:22.776 position:50% align:center
Why are you guys
talking like that?

00:07:22.859 --> 00:07:24.194 position:50% align:center
What's the point?

00:07:24.277 --> 00:07:26.863 position:50% align:center
Why bother being nice to
someone I'm not interested in?

00:07:26.946 --> 00:07:28.490 position:50% align:center
'Cause that's how
you get popular!

00:07:28.573 --> 00:07:30.241 position:50% align:center
You'll end up sad and alone!

00:07:30.325 --> 00:07:33.161 position:50% align:center
Who cares? I never wanted
to be popular, anyway.

00:07:33.244 --> 00:07:34.996 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:07:35.080 --> 00:07:36.915 position:50% align:center
[HIROSHI]
Ooh! I wish I could say that!

00:07:36.998 --> 00:07:39.334 position:50% align:center
[YUSUKE]
Maybe one day I'll be that cool!

00:07:39.417 --> 00:07:41.461 position:50% align:center
What the hell is wrong
with you guys?

00:07:41.544 --> 00:07:43.004 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT A]
Why're you here?

00:07:43.088 --> 00:07:45.715 position:50% align:center
Think you can just show
up and get in my way?

00:07:45.799 --> 00:07:47.592 position:50% align:center
Come on. Admit it.

00:07:47.676 --> 00:07:49.135 position:50% align:center
You like Kyo, don't you?

00:07:49.219 --> 00:07:51.429 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI, KYO grunt]

00:07:51.513 --> 00:07:53.640 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI, KYO] Are you freakin'
kidding me with this?!

00:07:53.723 --> 00:07:55.517 position:50% align:center
I'm really sorry!
Please don't hurt me!

00:07:55.600 --> 00:07:57.644 position:50% align:center
[HIROSHI, YUSUKE]
I wanna be popular!

00:07:57.727 --> 00:08:00.021 position:50% align:center
Oh, dear. What did I miss?

00:08:00.105 --> 00:08:02.357 position:50% align:center
Um, is everything okay?

00:08:02.440 --> 00:08:04.150 position:50% align:center
[HANAJIMA]
Not to worry, Tohru.

00:08:04.234 --> 00:08:08.071 position:50% align:center
I have things well in hand here.
I was with them the entire time.

00:08:08.154 --> 00:08:10.615 position:50% align:center
[KYO] Liar, you were off
somewhere stuffing your face

00:08:10.699 --> 00:08:11.449 position:50% align:center
--for most of it.
--[UOTANI] Ugh!

00:08:11.533 --> 00:08:12.992 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
I'm so pissed off!

00:08:13.076 --> 00:08:16.287 position:50% align:center
Chick gets rejected and
she takes it out on me!

00:08:16.371 --> 00:08:17.414 position:50% align:center
I don't care what happens,

00:08:17.497 --> 00:08:19.624 position:50% align:center
I'm never gonna pull
that kinda crap!

00:08:19.708 --> 00:08:21.334 position:50% align:center
So, what's up?

00:08:21.418 --> 00:08:24.462 position:50% align:center
All that yelling--something
must have happened, right?

00:08:24.546 --> 00:08:27.716 position:50% align:center
Leave it. It's none
of your business.

00:08:27.799 --> 00:08:30.510 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU yelping]

00:08:30.593 --> 00:08:32.012 position:50% align:center
What was that for?

00:08:32.095 --> 00:08:34.514 position:50% align:center
Jeez, everyone's either yelling
at me or hitting me today!

00:08:34.597 --> 00:08:35.724 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
Good.

00:08:35.807 --> 00:08:38.018 position:50% align:center
You deserve it, you idiot!

00:08:38.977 --> 00:08:41.312 position:50% align:center
That was exactly
the right response.

00:08:41.396 --> 00:08:42.939 position:50% align:center
Care for some <i>dango</i> ?

00:08:43.023 --> 00:08:44.232 position:50% align:center
Yes, thank you.

00:08:44.315 --> 00:08:46.943 position:50% align:center
Wha--? Why? Yuki?

00:08:48.820 --> 00:08:50.739 position:50% align:center
[KYO]
It's none of your business.

00:08:52.741 --> 00:08:54.117 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU] It's not like
that's the first time

00:08:54.200 --> 00:08:59.956 position:50% align:center
someone's said that to me...
but it made my heart ache.

00:09:00.040 --> 00:09:03.376 position:50% align:center
Just like it did up on the roof.

00:09:04.794 --> 00:09:06.171 position:50% align:center
[CLERK A]
Can I help you find something?

00:09:06.254 --> 00:09:07.922 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU gasps]

00:09:08.006 --> 00:09:11.593 position:50% align:center
No. I'm fine, thanks.
Have a nice day!

00:09:12.719 --> 00:09:14.596 position:50% align:center
[sighs]

00:09:14.679 --> 00:09:15.513 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:09:15.597 --> 00:09:17.057 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU]
Huh?

00:09:17.140 --> 00:09:20.060 position:50% align:center
Everyone must've moved on while
I was in there spacing out!

00:09:20.143 --> 00:09:21.603 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU]
Huh?

00:09:21.686 --> 00:09:25.690 position:50% align:center
[CAT meowing]

00:09:31.780 --> 00:09:32.989 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU]
Kyo, hey.

00:09:33.073 --> 00:09:36.451 position:50% align:center
[KYO]
Hm? Oh, hey.

00:09:36.534 --> 00:09:41.539 position:50% align:center
So, um, you're not going
to shop for souvenirs?

00:09:41.623 --> 00:09:43.166 position:50% align:center
With that crowd, no way.

00:09:43.249 --> 00:09:45.585 position:50% align:center
Too much of a chance
I'll transform.

00:09:45.669 --> 00:09:48.630 position:50% align:center
Heh. Good point.
I forgot about that.

00:09:48.713 --> 00:09:51.633 position:50% align:center
Well, souvenirs aren't
my thing, anyway.

00:09:51.716 --> 00:09:53.426 position:50% align:center
I'll just hang here
till they're done.

00:09:53.510 --> 00:09:55.303 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU]
What an adorable cat.

00:09:55.387 --> 00:09:57.514 position:50% align:center
It looks like you've made
a new friend, Kyo

00:09:57.597 --> 00:09:59.099 position:50% align:center
[KYO]
Yeah, not so much.

00:09:59.182 --> 00:10:02.477 position:50% align:center
I told you, they just
come up to me sometimes.

00:10:02.560 --> 00:10:04.145 position:50% align:center
[meows]

00:10:04.229 --> 00:10:06.356 position:50% align:center
Ah! You okay?

00:10:14.572 --> 00:10:16.241 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU]
Aww. Come back, kitty!

00:10:16.324 --> 00:10:19.119 position:50% align:center
Oh, no, what should we do?
We need to go after it!

00:10:19.202 --> 00:10:22.414 position:50% align:center
The cat came over on its
own and left on its own.

00:10:22.497 --> 00:10:23.915 position:50% align:center
